<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2864: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-24T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 24,
                                            1920—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>190. Your No. 180, July 11, noon.<note n="69" xml:id="d546fn69"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_548">p.
                                    548</ref>.</note> Department does not believe it advisable that
                                applications of Chinese Government for loans under the Consortium
                                should be made to the Legation. More orderly method would be for
                                Chinese Government to apply to the four Group representatives in
                                Peking.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>